+// Week 3 entry body. Plain JSX (no MDX setup) so content lives in the same
+// toolchain as the rest of the app. Styles are inherited from the journal
+// article container — see pages/JournalEntryPage.tsx.
+
+export function Week3() {
+  return (
+    <>
+      <p>
+        Three weeks ago I exited Scaile (in great hands with Simon now) and
+        started Floom. Every Friday I'll publish raw notes — what I shipped,
+        what I learned, what I got wrong. No narrative arc, no polish. If
+        that's useful, subscribe.
+      </p>
+
+      <h2>The thesis, in one line</h2>
+      <p>
+        Look at Paperclip.ing and similar products. I don't hear people saying
+        they want an AI CEO and CMO team of agents. They just want AI to take
+        over the things they do manually right now — and it's a huge struggle,
+        because the space is full of ambiguity.
+      </p>
+      <p>
+        That's the gap. Floom is the{' '}
+        <strong>production layer for mass-adopted agent work</strong>: the
+        security, access control, and digestible UI that turns frontier agent
+        capability into something 2 billion people can actually use, not just
+        10 million early adopters.
+      </p>
+
+      <h2>Where I actually am</h2>
+      <p>Pre-revenue by design. Disentangling the MVP in the open.</p>
+      <ul>
+        <li>
+          <strong>ARR:</strong> €0
+        </li>
+        <li>
+          <strong>Clients:</strong> 0
+        </li>
+        <li>
+          <strong>Team:</strong> 1 FTE (me)
+        </li>
+        <li>
+          <strong>Product:</strong> MVP WIP. Will untangle and ship versions
+          one by one.
+        </li>
+        <li>
+          <strong>Runway:</strong> F&amp;F round opening soon.
+        </li>
+        <li>
+          <strong>Location:</strong> Made it to SF (F.inc Canopy). Prepping
+          O-1 visa.
+        </li>
+      </ul>
+
+      <h2>What I did this week</h2>
+      <ul>
+        <li>
+          Talked to ~50 people. ~80% fit the broad ICP. The pain is real, the
+          articulation of it is not.
+        </li>
+        <li>
+          Co-ideated with Paul Schraven, Vlad, and Falco Schneider.
+        </li>
+        <li>
+          Had a trial with a strong dev in Berlin for the co-founder slot.
+          Didn't click on scope. Search continues.
+        </li>
+        <li>
+          Gave three speaker sessions: AI Beavers, Don't Gate, TechLabs.
+        </li>
+        <li>
+          Joined Don't Gate as AI Advisor — stays close to the customer I'm
+          building Floom for.
+        </li>
+        <li>Started prepping the O-1.</li>
+      </ul>
+
+      <h2>What I learned</h2>
+      <p>
+        <strong>
+          Creator-operators are struggling to get their teams onboard with
+          agents.
+        </strong>{' '}
+        This is exactly the problem I expected coming in. What I didn't expect
+        is how <em>early</em> the ambiguity sits — it's not "which tool," it's
+        "what is even the unit of work an agent should own." I need to
+        disentangle this before I build more.
+      </p>
+      <p>
+        <strong>
+          The field isn't as crowded as the Twitter timeline makes it look.
+        </strong>{' '}
+        Every frontier lab is coming at every layer at once — research, coding,
+        consumer, team infra. No one can win all four categories simultaneously.
+        The production layer — hardcoded use cases, security, access control,
+        digestible UI — is wide open and undervalued because it's unglamorous.
+      </p>
+      <p>
+        <strong>
+          Berlin has builder energy I didn't know I was missing.
+        </strong>{' '}
+        Hyper-connected, generous, fast. Hope to find the same thing in SF now.
+      </p>
+
+      <h2>What I got wrong</h2>
+      <p>
+        I underestimated how much user-pain discovery I still need. I was
+        starting to architect before I had enough pain interviews.
+        Course-correcting: a lot more discovery this week.
+      </p>
+
+      <h2>Next week</h2>
+      <ul>
+        <li>10+ more pain interviews.</li>
+        <li>
+          First Build Friday with the AI Beavers crew — planning to run it in
+          SF.
+        </li>
+        <li>
+          Open a Discord for contributors (separate from the one for users — I
+          want both but they're different conversations).
+        </li>
+        <li>First F&amp;F conversations.</li>
+        <li>Start untangling the MVP into shippable slices.</li>
+      </ul>
+
+      <h2>Help I need</h2>
+      <ul>
+        <li>
+          <strong>Intros to creator-operators</strong> running 5–50 person
+          teams who are actively trying (and struggling) to roll out agent
+          work internally. Reply to this email.
+        </li>
+        <li>
+          <strong>A co-founder.</strong> Technical, product-minded, wants to
+          own the production layer problem with me. SF or Berlin.
+        </li>
+      </ul>
+
+      <p>See you next Friday.</p>
+      <p>— Federico</p>
+    </>
+  );
+}
